{
  "stem": "5275.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] But after one week, marvelous week, I went back to Kielce, and-- and was there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My mother writes me a letter saying she found an agricultural school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was the only school still allowed in Poland during that time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And she knew that in that agricultural school, even though they were teaching you the agriculture, they still teached you subjects like physics and mathematics and others.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Somehow, again, she found the money to pay for my schooling and she told me to go there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "She told me where it was, she enrolled me there, and I should go there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Trzyciarz, what I hate even to spell it for you, to you, T-R-Z-Y-C-I-A-R-Z-- a small village.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I went there, and it was lucky I did, because after the war I went back to those people in Kielce I lived with, they told me that one week after I left, Gestapo came looking for me.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They already knew that my papers were false, because they already entered the Russian zone and they already-- and the Gestapo was amazing, they had-- they didn't have computers at those times, but they were absolutely amazing in following through on those things.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And they went there, they found out no such person wasn't ever there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was in the school and this was a marvelous time for me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Plenty of food to eat, work, but I was learning things.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was A student in physics, and chemistry, and algebra, and so on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were about, oh, a dozen students there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We lived in a dormitory.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I shared a room with three other-- two other kids.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Made good friends with them.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
